DURBAN – SANDF soldiers from the 4 Artillery Regiment confiscated goods worth more than R1 million in Limpopo in recent operations.SANDF Captain Moses Semono said now that the water in the mighty Limpopo River had subsided,  criminals had started with their illegal activities of undermining the sovereignty of South Africa.“SANDF soldiers confiscated R838 963 worth of illicit cigarettes at Yellow Gate on the Northern side of Musina Town,” Semono said.He said their counterparts at Gate 7, confiscated four boats worth R10 000 and also arrested undocumented persons who were in one boat.“In Pontdrift, on the Western side of Musina Town, soldiers confiscated illicit cigarettes valued at R301 299 on the R572, while they were busy with foot patrols. Except for the incident of the boats, the suspects managed to evade arrest on the other two,” Semono said.MORE ON THISWATCH: R1bn worth of counterfeit goods seized at Durban harbourLOOK: SANDF confiscate illegal cigarettes worth R1.4m and dagga along SA/Zimbabwe borderPICS & VIDEO: Illegal skin lightening products worth over R14m seized“In total, members of 4 Artillery Regiment confiscated goods worth R 1 150 262.”SANDF soldiers confiscate more than a million rand worth of illegal cigarettes in Limpopo. | Captain KutumelaMeanwhile, on Wednesday, SANDF soldiers averted a possible ATM explosion when they confiscated several explosives valued at about R38 000 from three undocumented persons, all Zimbabwean nationals, on the western side of the Beitbridge border post.Semono said the suspects were entering South Africa illegally, carrying 65 blasting cartridges of superpower 90 emulsion explosives together with connector capped fuses, as well as reels of detonating cor​​ds.“The bomb disposal unit from the SAPS in Musina was activated, and thereafter took over further investigations.”Daily News